<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>eclipse on technical_</title><link>https://blog.agramakov.me/tags/eclipse/</link><description>Recent content in eclipse on technical_</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language/><lastBuildDate>Sun, 08 Jul 2018 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.agramakov.me/tags/eclipse/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Configure Visual Studio toolchain on Eclipse</title><link>https://blog.agramakov.me/posts/2018/07-08-configure-visual-studio-toolchain-on-eclipse/</link><pubDate>Sun, 08 Jul 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.agramakov.me/posts/2018/07-08-configure-visual-studio-toolchain-on-eclipse/</guid><description><p>1. Install software:</p><ul><li><p><a href="http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/packages/eclipse-ide-cc-developers/oxygen3a" target="_blank">Eclipse IDE for C/C++ Developers</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/" target="_blank">Visual Studio</a></p></li></ul><p>2.<strong>Open</strong> Eclipse -> Help -> Install New Software&hellip; -></p><p>Work with:Â <code>http://download.eclipse.org/tools/cdt/releases/9.4/</code> -></p><p>CDT Optional Features -> C/C++ Visual C++ Support 9.4.3.201802261533</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_67.png" alt="screen_eclipse_67.png"/></p><p>-> Next -> Agree -> Install -> Finish -> Restart</p><p>3.<strong>Close</strong> Eclipse</p><p>4.<strong>Open</strong> Developer Command Prompt for VS 2017 and run from it Eclipse (this trick will add all needed VS environment variables to path)</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_cmd_66.png" alt="screen_cmd_66.png"/></p><p>5. Create new C++ project</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_68.png" alt="screen_68.png"/></p><p>6. Open Project Properties</p><p>C/C++ General -> Paths and Symbols -> Includes -> Add&hellip; -></p><blockquote><p><code>${VSINSTALLDIR}/VC/Tools/MSVC/14.11.25503/include</code></p></blockquote><p>+ Add to all configurations</p><p>+ Add to all languages</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_69.png" alt="screen_eclipse_69.png"/></p><p>7. Ok -> Apply and Close -> Yes</p><p>8. Build</p><p>9. Run -> Run configurations</p><ul><li><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_70.png" alt="screen_eclipse_70.png"/></li><li>C/C++ Application -><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_71.png" alt="screen_eclipse_71.png"/></li><li>Run</li></ul><p>10. Done!</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_72.png" alt="screen_eclipse_72.png"/></p></description></item></channel></rss>